# Shader sources are byte-input to the compiler: pin LF in the repo AND in the
# working tree so the same fixture feeds identical bytes on every OS (the
# byte-identity tests normalize EOLs defensively, but the checkout should not
# vary in the first place). Verified before adding (git ls-files --eol): every
# tracked *.fx / *.fxh is already index-LF, so this renormalizes nothing.
*.fx  text eol=lf
*.fxh text eol=lf

# Compiled shader containers and WASM modules are binary — never EOL-converted,
# never diffed as text. (Already auto-detected as binary today; pinned so a
# future text-looking blob can't be silently mangled.)
*.mgfx binary
*.fxb  binary
*.wasm binary
